    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1976-06-02T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1976-06-02T08:18:00-05:00" n="52"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                <head>52. Memorandum of Conversation<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d52fn1">
                        <p>
                            <seg type="summary">Summary: <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1"
                                    >Kissinger</persName> informed <persName corresp="#p_FGR_1"
                                    >Ford</persName> of <persName corresp="#p_SA_1"
                                >Sadat</persName>’s desire to eliminate <persName corresp="#p_QM_1"
                                    >Qadhafi</persName>.</seg>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <seg type="source">Source: Library of Congress, Manuscript Division,
                                Kissinger Papers, Box CL 283, Memoranda of Conversations,
                                Presidential File. Secret; <gloss target="#t_Nodis_1">Nodis</gloss>.
                                The meeting took place in the Oval Office.</seg>
                        </p>
                    </note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        from="1976-06-02T09:18:00-04:00" to="1976-06-02T10:00:00-04:00"
                        type="conversation-or-meeting-date">June 2, 1976, 9:18–10:00 a.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>President <persName corresp="#p_FGR_1">Ford</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Dr. <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>, Secretary
                        of State</item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SBC_1">Brent Scowcroft</persName>, Assistant to the
                        President for National Security Affairs</item>
                </list>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion unrelated to Libya.]</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName>: <persName corresp="#p_SA_1"
                        >Sadat</persName> wants to overthrow <persName corresp="#p_QM_1"
                        >Qadhafi</persName>. [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line not
                        declassified</hi>]</p>
                <p>President: They have wanted to for a long time. What do they want from us?</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName>: He wants us to screen the
                    Soviets from moving into Libya, aerial photos of Libya, and contact with the
                    Sixth Fleet. They don’t. . . .</p>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion unrelated to Libya.]</p>
            </div>
